testOneTripleWithRelativeUri

public void testOneTripleWithRelativeUri()
                                  throws IOException,
                                         org.apache.any23.extractor.ExtractionException,
                                         org.apache.any23.writer.TripleHandlerException
Checks that a triple with absolute URI nodes for subject and predicate and relative URI node for object from the sample RDF appears in the accumulated triples after extraction. The literal node has the form of a relative URI, and Fedora's Resource Index does not contemplate such URIs, so we treat it as a literal.

Throws:
IOException
org.apache.any23.extractor.ExtractionException
org.apache.any23.writer.TripleHandlerException

testSetContentLength

public void testSetContentLength()
We do not implement setContentLength() because there is no need for it in the Fedora context.
